        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 3:24PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 324 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking an area of strong
thunderstorms 6 miles west of Pryor, or 25 miles south of Billings,
moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fromberg, Pryor and Crow Indian Reservation.

This statement does not include Billings.
</description>
        <instruction>This storm may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional
information and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.

Persons in campgrounds should consider seeking sturdy shelter until
this storm passes.</instruction>
